However, Slate expresses disappointment, feeling that the series falls short compared to other spy productions. Forbes focuses on Fassbender's passion for his craft, while the Financial Times provides a nuanced review, highlighting the slippery nature of the spy thriller genre. Men's Health emphasizes Fassbender's ability to challenge viewers' perspectives. The Hollywood Reporter reviews the show as a whole, providing an overview of its strengths and weaknesses. Yahoo News UK explores the perspectives of Fassbender and co-star Jeffrey Wright on the complexities of espionage. Radio Times discusses the availability of the show in the UK. Despite the mixed reviews, Screen Rant acknowledges the low Rotten Tomatoes score, indicating that the show has not universally impressed critics.
